<p>Sending passwords over email or text may seem easy, but it leaves a permanent record that could be exposed if those messages are ever compromised. With Password Pusher, we avoid that risk by creating secure, one-time links that automatically expire after use. This way, sensitive information isnâ€™t left sitting in inboxes or chat histories. To send your username and password securely, just follow these steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Send us the username via email or text.</li>
  <li>Enter the password you want to share into the password field.</li>
  <li>Set expiration options:
    <ul>
      <li>Expire after 1 day</li>
      <li>Limit to 1 view</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Enable additional security settings by checking:
    <ul>
      <li>âœ… â€œUse a 1-click retrieval stepâ€</li>
      <li>âœ… â€œAllow immediate deletionâ€</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Add a passphrase to protect the download link (remember and copy this passphrase).</li>
  <li>Click â€œPush Itâ€ to generate the secure link.</li>
  <li>Copy the link or QR code and share it with the us.</li>
  <li>Send the passphrase and the link separately using different communication methods.
    <ul>
      <li>Example: Send the passphrase via text message and the link via email.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

